  "description": "A quotient group is what you get when you take a [group](./group.md) and \"collapse\" part of it — treating certain elements as identical. The elements you collapse form a [normal subgroup](./normal-subgroup.md), and the quotient group consists of the [cosets](./coset.md) of that subgroup, with a natural group operation inherited from the original group.",
